cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SI 

This paper proposes a novel approach for designing and training deep neural networks using polynomial-based approximations. The focus is on improving the initialization of network parameters for gradient descent-based training methods. This topic is closely related to machine learning (cs.LG), neural networks (cs.NE), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also considers numerical examples related to computer vision (cs.CV) and computational intelligence (cs.SI).
